fields.historical_context_note:
Rewards: n/a
Forfeits: n/a
No. of Players: any
Equipment required: see further description

Rules:
The illusions are divided among the sets as Diamond Depth Perception, Heart Figure Ground Illusions and Unstable Figures, Spades Seeing What Is Not There or Not Seeing What Is There and Clubs Size and Figure Distortion.  The picture cards and aces also have different illusions - Aces Illusions of Color, Kings Color Reversal, Queens Ambiguous Figures, Jacks Impossible Figures.
Joker hsows a marked head profile with COPYRIGHT 1984 Y & B ASSOCIATES INC underneath on one side and on the other side some of the answers to the illusions.
Explanation card with some answers on one side and on the other details about Kellogg's and the game together with C 1990 KELLOGG COMPANY ILLUSTRATIONS REPRODUCED BY KIND PERMISSION OF INTERCOL LTD C 1987 INTERCOL.
Explanation card with some answers on one side and on the other details about visual illusions titled CAN YOU BELIEVE YOUR EYES? by Dr. J R Block and Dr. Harold E Yuker Holstra University  C INTERCOL LONDON
